<div class="govuk-grid-column-full">

    <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p class="govuk-body">This accessibility statement applies to the 'Apply for  a felling licence' service.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body">This website is run by the Forestry Commission. We want as many people as possible to be able to use this website. </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">For example, that means you should be able to:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>change colours, contrast levels and fonts</li>
        <li>navigate most of the website using just a keyboard</li>
        <li>navigate most of the website using speech recognition software</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">We’ve also made the website text as simple as possible to understand.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body"><a class="govuk-link" href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/">AbilityNet</a> has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How accessible this website is</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">We know some parts of this website are not fully accessible for:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>users who need to zoom in or increase the size of the text, the content will not reflow in a single column</li>
        <li>users who use screen-readers, most older PDF documents are not fully accessible</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Known issues with this website</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">We are aware of the following accessibility issues within the service:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>
            On some pages (such as ‘Create a Property’ and ‘Felling Details’), we use radio buttons to reveal additional content. 
            These buttons use the aria-expanded attribute but do not include an ARIA role such as menuitemradio, which is required for screen reader support.
        </li>
        <li>
            This means the component may not be interpreted correctly by some assistive technologies and does not meet 
			<a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/name-role-value.html">
				WCAG 2.1 success criterion 4.1.2: Name, Role, Value</a>.
                We have followed the 
            <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/radios/#conditionally-revealing-radios">
                GOV.UK Design System guidance for radios with conditionally revealing content</a>, 
                but recognise that this approach may result in invalid HTML. 
                We are monitoring guidance and exploring alternatives to improve compliance.
        </li>
		<li>
            On the ‘Create a Compartment’ page, users cannot interact with the map using a keyboard. This does not meet
            <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/keyboard.html">
                WCAG 2.2 success criterion 2.1.1: Keyboard</a>.
		</li>
        <li>
            Also on the ‘Create a Compartment’ page, the tab order of the map controls is not logical. 
            When users reveal new options, the keyboard focus does not move to them in a usable order. This does not meet 
            <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/keyboard.html">
                WCAG 2.2 success criterion 2.4.3: Focus Order</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
            This site uses a third-party component for user registration. On some pages in the user sign up/sign in flows there is use of
            HTML list elements to represent a form. This may affect how some assistive technologies interpret the content, and does not meet 
            <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/info-and-relationships.html">
                WCAG 2.2 success criterion 1.3.1: Info and relationships
            </a>.
        </li>
	</ul>
    <p class="govuk-body">We will continue to update this accessibility statement as we fix these issues.</p>

